Author: phm87#7395
Content: Make a listunspent to see all addys with coins then make dumpprivkey on each Raddy. Do not share privkeys, keep them secret

Author: phm87#7395
Content: If there are too many, you should consolidate first, i.e. send all coins to 1 addy, wait for the tx to be confirmed then dumpprivkey

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> @pal are you able to start up an old Hush wallet? That is how you can dump a private key. If you have it all in one or a few addresses, that is the best way

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> it doesn't need to sync, or download the chain. it hopefully should be able to let you dump a key. But I recognize all this ain't easy

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> @pal you should use your wallet.dat, the old one, with SilentDragon

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> :SD: will make a brand new wallet.dat for you when it starts. Move that out of the way, and put your old wallet.dat in place, then restart and then go into the Advanced options and ask it to "rescan + reindex" if you still don't see your balance.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Best thing to do is send all your funds to a new wallet.dat, it's not good to use the old wallet.dat indefinitely. Just to sweep funds. And yes, none of this is easy

Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> feel free to ask more questions here

Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> @gilardh fyi wallet.dat is a binary format, it's actually a BerkeleyDB format database
